Horrible service. One person working, so while I was waiting by the register being ignored he was working on mobile orders that were coming in as I was standing there. Let me clarify, there were two stickers waiting, so that meant there were 2 drinks for mobile orders pending, but while he was making those drinks more stickers popped up that he decided to make before tending to me. And they just kept coming. Eventually a woman comes out to help him (she was obviously quicker at making drinks) and she takes over drinks while he looks at the orders and starts heating up sandwiches and pastries while I'm still standing there and mobile orders continue to print out ahead of me.  Finally, after I get to order and am waiting for my drink, a guy who picked up his mobile order of two drinks and a sandwich or pastry, comes back inside interrupts the barista and says he forgot to ask for whipped cream for his dog. So she stops, even though there is a back up of orders in addition to me and 2 other people who ordered in store, still waiting for drinks. Does it matter that this guy is tall and white, while I'm short and Hispanic, I don't know. Probably not, but at that moment I can tell you that it felt like it mattered and added to my frustration. I'm sure he would tell you he had great customer service. But I don't think he would have had an issue if he would been told to wait until they caught up to orders time stamped within the last 15 min.  So in the end about 12 people (some with more than one drink) and a dog got their drinks before me. I usually order using their app, but I shouldn't be punished if I don't use it.
